  "prompt": "What are the symptoms of eczema?",
  "response": "Eczema (atopic dermatitis) symptoms include:\n\n1. Skin symptoms:\n- Dry, sensitive skin\n- Red or brownish-gray patches\n- Intense itching\n- Raised, rough, or scaly skin\n- Swollen or raw skin from scratching\n\n2. Location of symptoms:\n- Face\n- Hands\n- Feet\n- Wrists\n- Ankles\n- Upper chest\n- Neck\n- Inside of elbows\n- Behind knees\n\n3. Additional characteristics:\n- Skin may crack or bleed\n- Skin can become thickened (lichenification)\n- Blisters or oozing/weeping in severe cases\n- Skin infections may develop\n\n4. Symptom variations:\n- Symptoms can come and go\n- Flare-ups triggered by stress, allergens, or environmental factors\n- Symptoms may be worse at night\n- Can vary in intensity from mild to severe\n\n5. Age-related differences:\n- Infants: Often on cheeks and scalp\n- Children: Typically in skin folds\n- Adults: More likely on hands and potential widespread coverage\n\nConsulting a healthcare professional is recommended for proper diagnosis and treatment.",
